<headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 28 at 4:01AM CST  by NWS Chicago</headline>
<description>...Patchy Freezing Fog with Possible Slick Spots this Morning...
Patchy fog, some dense, will continue into the start of the
morning commute in parts of the Fox River Valley to the Illinois
River Valley area, as well as toward Pontiac. Visibility within
the fog in spotty places is near one quarter mile. Of particular
note is that temperatures are below freezing across this area,
which will likely result in patchy slick spots especially on
overpasses and bridges.
Please allow extra travel time this morning and use heightened
caution. When driving, allow sufficient distance between you and
the car ahead of you. Also use your low beam headlights if
encountering dense fog.</description>
